# EAS Android AAB Versioning

Before generating any Android AAB for `expert-expo-app`, always verify and increment release versions in both Expo config and native Android config.

- Update `expert-expo-app/app.json`:
  - `expo.version` must be bumped for the release.
  - `expo.android.versionCode` must be higher than every previously uploaded Play Console build.
- If `expert-expo-app/android/` exists, EAS uses native Android values. Also update `expert-expo-app/android/app/build.gradle`:
  - `defaultConfig.versionCode` must match or exceed `app.json` and must never reuse an old Play Console version code.
  - `defaultConfig.versionName` must match `expo.version`.
- Before starting `npm run build:android:store` or `eas build --platform android --profile production`, run a quick verification that prints both sources and confirms they are in sync.
- Never upload an AAB unless EAS build details show the expected `appVersion` and `appBuildVersion`.

